From 55ce53d45ce16f9c084353fb400c0f2c16a6ec32 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Stan <stanbontrager@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Feb 2026 15:58:47 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/5] Phase 2: Add category enable checks to all active cheats

Entry 6 in Project_Development.md:

Added CheatContext helper methods:
- Added 8 category check methods (IsPlayerAndToolsEnabled(), etc.)

Updated 26 active cheats across all categories:
- Player & Tools: 8 cheats (InfiniteHealth, InfiniteStamina, etc.)
- Farm & Fishing: 14 cheats (AutoWater, DurableFences, FastMachines, Grow, etc.)
- Relationships: 2 cheats (AlwaysGiveGifts, NoFriendshipDecay)
- Time: 1 cheat (FreezeTime)
- Skills/Warps/Weather/Advanced: Action-based, handled by menu system

Implementation pattern: Each cheat's OnConfig now checks:
  needsUpdate = context.IsCategoryEnabled() && context.Config.FeatureToggle

Result: When category disabled, cheats don't register for updates
Backward compatible: All categories default to enabled
No build errors: Compilation verified successful

Next: Phase 3 - Expand GMCM integration to expose category toggles
